 Claus armed with\ngifts for the little ones and large\nbaskets filled with provisions for\nChristmas dinner.\nThe baskets and gifts were\nmade possible through the coop\neration of the couhty churches,\nbusiness men and fraternal or\nganizations.\nThe baskets were loaded into a\ntruck and two automobiles and\nunder the supervision of Mrs. Mae\nJacobs, superintendent of the\nArlington County Welfare Board\nwere delivered to each of the\nhomes.\nIn addition to this, members\nof the Ballston Klan. No. 6, meet\ning in the field at the intersec\ntion of the Wilson Boulevard and\nClements Avenue last night de\nlivered more than 50 other bas\nkets.\nCulpeper Legion Post\nSponsors Xmas Fete\nCULPEPER, Va., Dec. 25.\u2014A* a\nresult of much work on the part\nof Culpeper Post No. 44, American\nLegion, there was happiness in\nmany homes where Santa Claus\nheretofore has been a stranger.\nSeven members of the post de\nlivered toys of all kinds to 135\nchildren who otherwise would\nhave known little of Christmas.\nBesides the toys for the children\n30 baskets of food were delivered\nto needy families.\nThe post erected a large com\nmunity Christmas tree and last\nnight gave 1.250 stockings, filled\nwith candy and fruit, to the chil\ndren.\nChoirs from all the churches in\nCulpeper led the singing of Christ\nmas carols at the tree.\nArlington C. of C.\nWill Elect January 10\nCLERENDON, Va., Dec. 30.\u2014\nPlans by the board of. directors\nof the Arlington County Cham\nber of Commerce are being com\npleted for the holding of the\nannual meeting and election of\nofficers which has been an\nnounced for the night of Jan\nuary 10.' The meeting will be\nheld in the auditorium of the\"\nWashington Lee High School at.\n3 o\u2019clock.\nWith the resignation of P. P.\nWoodbridge as executive secre\ntary effective January 15, it is\nlearned that applications for\npart-time secretary are being\nreceived at the office M the\norganization.\nDollar Liner Damaged\nBy Fire at Singapore\nLONDON, Dec. 31 (INR.).\u2014\nThe Dollar Line Steamship Presi\ndent Van Buren was damaged\ntoday by fire at her dock in\nSingapore,. according to reports\nreceived in shipping circles here.\nThe cause of the fire and extent\nof thj damage are not known.\nPTOMAINE POISONING\nJohn Engle, <2, of the 300 block\nT St. N. E., a fireman attached to\nthe Number 9 Engkie Company,\nwas taken suddenly ID at the sta\ntion hduse early today tod-taken\nto Emergency Hospital, where Dr.\nI. Rutkoski, staff physician, said\nhis illness was due to ptomaine\npoisoning.\nGRAINS UNEVEN\nCHI CAOO. D\u00bbc. tI.N.S.).\u2014\nGrain* war, uneven today. Wheat waff\ndown M to l%r; corn unchanged' to\ntic Up and oats unchanged.\nOpening prieea:\nWh*\u00abt\u2014December. Al.llt March,\nIt.acfcOl.Sl; May, I1.UO1..I*: July.\n11. IS\nCorn\u2014December. Illife: March. Ilfce\nMU; May, MfccOlftfc;/July, 91He.\nOat*-r-Decembar, nona; March. 4tfcc;\nMay.llfca\nW. B. HIBBS CO.\n.The ONLY New York Stock Exchange House\nHaving Its Main Office in Washington\nMEMBERS\nNew -York. Stock Exchange\nBoston Stock Exchange\nPhiladelphia Stock Exchange\nWashington Stock Exchange\nNew York Cotton Exchange\nChicago Board of Trade\nAmerican Bankers Association\nDistrict Bankers Association\nHIBBS BUILDING\nWASHINGTON, D. C.\nTHURSDAY, DECEMBER S 6, 1929\nBOND MARKET\n(Furnished by W. Hibbo A Xo.)\nDomestic Bondi\nAtchison, Topeka ASF ta.\nAtlantic Refining 15...*.... 1\u00bbJ\nAmer Agriculture Chem 7%5..., 1\u00bbJ\nAllis ChalmOrs Is \u00bb\u00bbH\nAmer Smelters la\nAmor Tel A Tel 4tos.. U\u00bb\nAmer Tel A Tel la IM to\nAmor Tel A Tel Itos IW\n801 l Tel Pa Is \u20194l IM to\nBrooklyn Man Trans la >4\nBaltimore A Ohio 4s \u00bb1\nBaltimore A Ohio Ito\nBethlehem Steel la IM\nChicago A Alton M\nChicago A Northwestern 4to\u00ab-.. \u00bb\u00bbM\nCHI Rock Island 4to\u00ab--. Mto\nConsolidated Gas Ito*--\nDodge Motors Is M\nDenver A Rio Grande Tito\nDetroit Edison Is\nErie Ry 5s Mto\nGoodyear Tiro A Rub M........ Ilfc\nGoodri