gogue.\nA permanent rabbi for the con\ngregation will be selected shortly\nafter the first of the year.\nGuest rabbis have been conduct\nink the services for several\nmonths, many of them among\nthe most prominent members of\nthe rabbinate.\nJoseph A. Wilner, president of\nthe congregation and Cantor\nLouis Novick will officiate at the\nservices tomorrow. He will also\nconduct the regular services Sat\nurday morning.\nHistorical Society Has\nAnnual Session at C. U;\nThe American Catholic His\ntorical Society will open its tenth\nannual meeting in McMahon\nHall, Catholic University, tomor\nrow morning. The meeting,\nwhich will end Saturday night,\nwill be coincident with that of\nthe American Catholic Philo\nsophical Association.\nThe Rev. Dr. Edwin J. Ryan,\nof the Catholic University, will\nspeak at the opening session at\n9 o\u2019clock on the subject of \"Papal\nConcordats in Modem Times.\u201d\nOther speakers will be the Rt.\nRev. Philip Bernardini, the Rev.\nGilbert Carrahan, of St. Louis,\nand Clarence E. Martin, of\nMartinsburg, W. Va,\nHEN HOUSE ROBBED\nThieves last night stole nine\nchickens valued at 815 from the\nhen house in the rear yard of\nthe home of John Buzzano, 3300\nblock Dent Pl. N. W.\nBeatin* need* ar* *atl*fl*d th* year\n\u25a0renad through Tine* or Herald <3aa\n\u2022ified ad*.\n'\u25a0lllllll\n1 \u25bcwKi w>|Oryfrww!\u00bb\n/\u2022v?i\nRESORT\nH TRAVEL\nJM- Guide\n''gV 1929-1930\n\nzj. \u201c:SSSSS\u201ct\nPT\"7laiJ|\nUselt\nwimvAanon\nIN THE SOUTHLAND\nThis guide chock-full of the latest\nnews and announcements of Southern Re\nsorts and Hotels will aid you in selecting a\nsuitable Resort and Hotel at which to\nspend your winter vacation. Get it now\u2014\nFILL IN COUPON\nand\nMAIL TODAY\nt rSTw.rtiSrtX\u2019iSX:\nFor ruttrationa or addi- Waabtactea. D. C.\ntloaal information of any lactated pleat* ttad S\u00ab tar maHtaa\nWinter Retort or Hotel, call copy of you Winter HomM and Trarte\nDittrlot IMO and atk for Guido to\u2014\nRuort and Tra